 interpreted in terms of physics beyond\nthe Standard Model. The limits obtained on possible tensor type charged\ncurrents in the weak interaction hamiltonian are -0.045 $< (C_T+C'_T)/C_A <$\n0.159 (90\\% C.L.). The obtained limits are comparable to limits from other\ncorrelation measurements in nuclear $\\beta$ decay and contribute to further\nconstraining tensor coupling constants.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Sep 2014 14:47:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
